<subSubSection id="90C86550AD37B506FF722E98CAF1F9CB" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D86D36DBAD37B506FF722E98CAF1F9CB" blockId="89.[151,1437,1430,1745]" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">
<emphasis id="EAA6EAC9AD37B506FF722E98CB03FA66" bold="true" box="[151,274,1430,1456]" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species has a rugulose preepisternum, copper-red metasomal terga and striate gena and postgena, characteristics that separates it from other 
<taxonomicName id="1FD24D58AD37B506FD992EB5C93CFA03" authorityName="Eickwort" authorityYear="1969" box="[636,813,1467,1493]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Augochlora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Oxystoglossella">
<emphasis id="EAA6EAC9AD37B506FD992EB5C93CFA03" box="[636,813,1467,1493]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">Oxystoglossella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurring at the southernmost South America. 
<taxonomicName id="1FD24D58AD37B506FAAF2EB5CB40FA2F" authority="Lepeco &amp; Gonçalves, 2020" authorityName="Lepeco &amp; Gonçalves" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Augochlora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hestia" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Augochlora">
<emphasis id="EAA6EAC9AD37B506FAAF2EB5CB40FA2F" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">A. (Augochlora) hestia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="EAA6EAC9AD37B506FEBD2ED1CBA2FA2F" bold="true" box="[344,435,1503,1529]" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="F19557B2AD37B506FEBD2ED1CBA2FA2F" box="[344,435,1503,1529]" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is similar to this species in color pattern, but lacks the typical characteristics of the subgenus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="90C86550AD37B506FF222D28CBB4F9B3" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="D86D36DBAD37B506FF222D28CBB4F9B3" blockId="89.[151,1437,1430,1745]" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">
<emphasis id="EAA6EAC9AD37B506FF222D28CB5EF996" bold="true" box="[199,335,1574,1600]" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="1FD24D58AD37B506FEBD2D29C826F996" authorityName="Strand" authorityYear="1910" box="[344,567,1575,1601]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Augochlora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="morrae">
<emphasis id="EAA6EAC9AD37B506FEBD2D29C826F996" box="[344,567,1575,1601]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">Augochlora morrae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was redescribed by 
<bibRefCitation id="BC434B2AAD37B506FCC72D29CE74F997" author="Lepeco, A. &amp; Goncalves, R. B." box="[802,1125,1575,1601]" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" pagination="261 - 293" refId="ref75535" refString="Lepeco, A. &amp; Goncalves, R. B. (2020) New species of Augochlora (Oxystoglossella) Eickwort (Hymenoptera; Apoidea) from Northeastern Brazil with an identification key for the region. Zootaxa, 4802 (2), 261 - 293. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4802.2.3" type="journal article" year="2020">Lepeco &amp; Gonçalves (2020)</bibRefCitation>
, nests were studied by 
<bibRefCitation id="BC434B2AAD37B506FA972D29CBB0F9B3" author="Michener, C. D. &amp; Lange, R. B." pageId="89" pageNumber="90" pagination="473 - 505" refId="ref75931" refString="Michener, C. D. &amp; Lange, R. B. (1958) Observations on the behavior of Brazilian Halictid bees, III. University of Kansas Science Bulletin, 39, 473 - 505." type="journal article" year="1958">Michener &amp; Lange (1958)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
